'''Antipoaching''' is a term used to define the [[Anti-competitive practices|anti-competitive conduct]] of companies conspiring not to hire each other's employees.<ref>[https://www.cnet.com/news/apple-google-others-settle-anti-poaching-lawsuit-for-415-million/ Apple, Google, others settle antipoaching lawsuit for $415 million - CNET], September 3, 2015, Lance Whitney, ''cNet.com'', retrieved at 2 March 2017</ref>

