'''Arnoud, Count<ref>http://trends.knack.be/economie/mensen/arnoud-de-pret-verlaat-ab-inbev/article-normal-230525.html</ref> de Pret Roose de Calesberg''' is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] noble businessman. He is a member of board of the international [[brewery]] [[InBev]], [[Delhaize]], [[Umicore]] and of [[Euronext]]-[[NYSE]].
== Family == Arnoud de Pret Roose de Calesberg is a descendant of [[Jacques I de Pret]], (1643-1703) grand almoner of Antwerp.<ref>Dictionnaire généalogique et héraldique des familles nobles du royaume de Belgique, Volume 4</ref> and related to count [[Philippe de Pret Roose]]. He is the grandson of a member of the house of [[Spoelberch|de Spoelberch]], an old [[Belgian nobility|Belgian noble house]], they are titled [[Viscount]] de Spoelberch. The house of Spoelberch is one of the three Belgian families to hold assets in [[Anheuser-Busch InBev]]. Arnoud de Pret Roose de Calesberg sit at the board of the giant beverage producer mainly to protect his family's assets.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.frerealbert.be/fortunes/de-spoelberch/inbev-brasse-les-plus-grosses-fortunes-de-belgique/|title=InBev brasse les plus grosses fortunes de Belgique|website=Frerealbert.be|date=21 December 2015|author=Marco Van Hees|language=fr|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://trends.levif.be/economie/people/ab-inbev-un-nouveau-representant-pour-les-familles/article-normal-200447.html|title=AB InBev : un nouveau représentant pour les familles|website=Levif.be|author=Jean-Luc Dehaene|language=fr|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref>
== Career == Arnoud de Pret Roose de Calesberg graduated as commercial engineer at the [[Louvain School of Management]] ([[Université Catholique de Louvain]] - UCL).<ref name="bloomberg 2219875">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=2219875&privcapId=874491|title=Executive profile: Arnoud de Pret Roose de Calesberg|website=Bloomberg.com|accessdate=11 September 2017}}</ref> He started his career in 1971 as credit officer at [[Morgan Guaranty Trust Company]]. From 1972 to 1978, he was corporate account manager at the [[Morgan Guaranty Trust Company]] of New York. In 1981, he became the treasurer of Belgian steel company CMrockerill-Sambre. From 1981 to 1990, he was treasurer and then as Chief Financial Manager for [[UCB (company)|UCB]].<ref name="bloomberg 2219875"/>
From 1991 until May 2000, he was Chief Financial Officer and a member of the board of directors and financial director of [[Umicore]]. Since 1990, he is also the Treasurer and Corporate Finance Manager at [[Société Générale de Belgique]].<ref name="bloomberg 2219875"/>
== Other mandates == * 2015 - 12 May 2016: Vice Chairman of The Supervisory Board at [[Euronext N.V.]]<ref name="bloomberg 2219875"/> * 1 July 2007 - 12 May 2016: Independent Member of Supervisory Board at [[Euronext N.V.]]<ref name="bloomberg 2219875"/> * 2005 - 30 April 2015: Director at [[UCB (company)|UCB]]<ref name="bloomberg 2219875"/> * 10 May 2000 - April 2015: Non-Executive Director of [[Umicore]] S.A.<ref name="bloomberg 2219875"/> * May 2002 - 26 May 2011: Independent Director of [[Louis Delhaize Group]]<ref name="bloomberg 2219875"/> * Since 1990: Director of [[Anheuser-Busch InBev]]<ref name="bloomberg 2219875"/>
