'''Luc Bossyns''' is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] businessman. He is managing director of [[Aquafin]], a [[Flanders|Flemish]] [[wastewater]] processing company.
==Education== He graduated as a [[civil engineer]] in naval engineering from [[Ghent University]]. In addition he also graduated in company management at the [[University of Antwerp]].
==Career== In 1977 he started his career as an engineer at Cockerill Yards Hoboken ([[Hoboken, Antwerp|Hoboken]]). First he worked with the [[Compagnie Maritime Belge]] (CMB) and with the Boelwerf [[shipyard]]. Luc Bossyns was director-general and director of Boelwerf Vlaanderen from 1993 until 1995 after which he went to work for Stork MEC.
During his position with the [[Boelwerf]], Bossyns was involved in a cause of fraud with government subsidies.<ref name="HLN">[http://www.nieuwsblad.be/Article/Detail.aspx?articleID=glu9th72 Bossyns blijft baas Aquafin ondanks fraude Boelwerf], Oktober 30, 2004</ref> He was convicted in 2004,<ref name="HLN" /> but subsequent appeals led to an acquittal of charges by lapse of time.<ref>[http://www.standaard.be/cnt/9320ifba "Geen straf voor fraude Boelwerf"], De Standaard, 18 September 2008</ref>
He has been managing director of [[Aquafin]] since May 2000.
==Sources== * [http://www.aquafin.be/nl/indexb.php?n=90&e=122&s=142 Luc Bossyns] (Aquafin) * [http://www.top500.de/details/348/aquafin_nv_belgium.php Aquafin] (Top 500)
