{{Infobox person |name = Luis Fernando Correa Bahamon |image = Luis Fernando Correa Bahamón.jpg |imagesize = |alt = |caption = |birth_date = 23 April 1955 |birth_place = [[Medellín]], [[Antioquia Department|Antioquia]], [[Colombia]] |death_date = |death_place = |nationality = [[Colombian people|Colombian]] |children = Daniel, Juan Camilo, Andres, Felipe ([[suicide]] Abril 2016) |alma_mater = [[Universidad Javeriana]], [[Xavier University]] |religion = }} {{Spanish name|Correa|Bahamon}}
'''Luis Fernando Correa Bahamon''' (born 23 April 1955) is a [[Colombian people|Colombian]] business man, philanthropist, and investor. He is an important leader in the hotel and construction industry in Colombia.
Correa is active in real-estate through his firms, Luis F. Correa y Asociados (Luis F. Correa and Associates), Real Estate Total, and NAI Colombia, parts of [[Red Empresarial Luis F. Correa]].<ref name=tormo>[http://www.tormo.com.co/noticias/5517/Un_Colombiano_Asumio_Por_Primera_Vez_Direccion_De_La_Federacion_Mundia.html Un Colombiano Asumió Por Primera Vez Dirección De La Federación Mundial De Inmobiliarios] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130101154558/http://www.tormo.com.co/noticias/5517/Un_Colombiano_Asumio_Por_Primera_Vez_Direccion_De_La_Federacion_Mundia.html |date=1 January 2013 }}</ref><ref name=europa>{{cite news |url=http://www.europe-re.com/system/main.php?pageid=2616&articleid=9102&objectid=10787 |title=Luis Fernando Correa Bahamon elected World President of FIABCI |date=18 June 2007 |publisher=[[FIABCI]]}}</ref> He is the owner of [[Wyndham Hotels & Resorts]] in Colombia through his company Diplomat Hotels,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.portafolio.co/negocios/otra-cadena-hotelera-se-instalara-bogota |title=Otra cadena hotelera se instalará en Bogotá |date=2 May 2011 |publisher=''Portafolio''}}</ref> has been involved in the development of the [[Sheraton Hotels and Resorts|Sheraton]] brand in Colombia and [[Ecuador]], and recently has managed the market entry of the [[Spain|Spanish]] hotel chain [[NH Hoteles]].<ref name=elspectador>{{cite news |url=http://www.elespectador.com/impreso/cuadernilloa/negocios/articuloimpreso-tras-el-boom-inmobiliario |title=Tras el ‘boom’ inmobiliario |author=Hugo Sabogal |date=10 April 2008 |publisher=[[el Spectador]]}}</ref> In 2010 he began a plan aiming to reinvent Colombia's hotel industry by building 100 hotels in 10 years.<ref name=elspectador/><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.portafolio.co/economia/%25E2%2580%2598vamos-hacer-100-hoteles-colombia%25E2%2580%2599-luis-fernando-corr |title=‘Vamos a hacer 100 hoteles en Colombia’: Luis Fernando Correa |date=22 February 2011 |publisher=''Portafolio''}}</ref> His contributions to the development of Colombia's economy have been noted by international leaders including [[President of Colombia]] [[Alvaro Uribe Velez]]<ref>{{cite web |url = http://web.presidencia.gov.co/sp/2007/agosto/21/08212007.html |title = Palabras del presidente Uribe en el congreso de Fedelonjas |author = [[Alvaro Uribe Velez]] |date = 21 August 2007 |publisher = [[President of Colombia]] |access-date = 19 August 2012 |archive-url = https://archive.is/20121128235700/http://web.presidencia.gov.co/sp/2007/agosto/21/08212007.html# |archive-date = 28 November 2012 |dead-url = yes |df = dmy-all }}</ref> and [[Republic of China President]] [[Ma Ying-jeou]].<ref name=myj>{{cite web |url=http://english.president.gov.tw/Default.aspx?tabid=491&itemid=19213 |title=President Ma Meets International Real Estate Federation World President Luis Correa-Bahamon |date=11 June 2008 |publisher=[[President of the Republic of China]]}}</ref>
Correa was honored as "Man of the Year" by construction and development magazine ''En Obra'', and was named "The King of Hotels" by ''Revista Dinero''.[5] Correa Bahamon was also the first Latin American to occupy the World Presidency of [[FIABCI]], the Paris-based International Real Estate Federation, following his 2007 election against Julia Clement.<ref name=tormo/><ref name=europa/><ref name=myj/><ref name=eltiempo>{{cite news |url=http://www.eltiempo.com/archivo/documento/CMS-3578801 |title=Correa Bahamón, elegido nuevo presidente mundial de la Fiabci en España |author=GABRIEL E. G. FLÓREZ |date=1 June 2007 |publisher=[[El Tiempo (Colombia)|el Tiempo]]}}</ref><ref name=fiabci>[http://www.fiabciuniversity.org/Faculty/bios/Luis%20Correa.pdf Luis Correa FIABCI bio]{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He simultaneously served as the federation's Regional President for the Americas, as well as a delegate to the [[United Nations Economic and Social Council]] representing the Federation as a special consultant.<ref name=europa/><ref name=fiabci/>
Luis Fernando Correa has written 5 books related to real estate.<ref name=elspectador/> He also has invested in several other business fields and through the Red Empresarial Luis F. Correa conglomerate is the owner of [[Lectorum Publications]], [[Scholastic Corporation]]'s Spanish-language book publisher, and Constructora Correas. He also is active in "Un Techo Para Colombia", a foundation dedicated to the construction of homes for the poor in Colombia, as well as The Global Housing Foundation, and The Scholarship Foundation.<ref name=tormo/>
Correa was born in [[Medellín]], Colombia. Before entering business he worked as a university professor and administrator as well as a public servant. He is a member of the US [[National Association of Realtors]].<ref name=eltiempo/> Correa has earned a [[BSc]] in [[Economics]] at [[Universidad Javeriana]] in [[Bogota]], and pursued graduate studies and an [[MBA]] at [[Xavier University]] in [[Cincinnati, Ohio]].<ref name=tormo/><ref name=elspectador/><ref name=fiabci/>
