[[Image:Bolinderska palatset Stockholm.JPG|thumb|right|300px|''SAF-borgen'' (right), the SAF headquarters from 1934 to 2001.]] The '''Swedish Employers Association''' ({{lang-sv|Svenska Arbetsgivareföreningen}}, commonly referred to as ''SAF''), was a Swedish [[employers' organization]] founded in 1902. SAF in 2001 merged with Sveriges Industriförbund (the ''Federation of Swedish Industries'') and formed [[Svenskt Näringsliv]] (''Confederation of Swedish Enterprise'').
